    {
      "id": "03af41d5_fb0b17f4",
      "file_path": "mod/component-json-schemas/component-specification/dcae-cli-v2/component-spec-schema.json",
      "patchset_number": 14,
      "line": 818,
      "message": "Pawel - Yes, my suggestion was to remove from spec file and have it included by default on bp-gen output (values can be defaulted to \"\" or some other string - which must overridden via bp- input).\n\nExcept for use_external_tls and external_cert_directory, all other new properties (ca_name, external_certificate_parameters), are not required from onboarding standpoint to be provided by a developer (as component_spec definition). Other properties seem more of deployment configuration and can be driven as blueprint input (this will provide delienation between design time and runtime properties).\n\n\nThe intent is a single spec can be used for onboarding MS into DCAE but used for multiple instantiation (with different deployment config). Binding those parameters in component_spec will require change each time when deploy configuration has to be modified.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 93,
        "name": "Vijay Venkatesh Kumar",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "vijayv81@gmail.com",
        "username": "vv770d"
      },
      "updated": "2020-07-02 14:48:19.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "73b0420e_11fe59d7",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "19a4e838_9a001724",
      "file_path": "mod/component-json-schemas/component-specification/dcae-cli-v2/component-spec-schema.json",
      "patchset_number": 15,
      "line": 810,
      "message": "If option1 (to consolidate truststore is adopted), which path will be used by the components (cert_directory or external_cert_directory) for retrieving the truststores?\n\nWould it make to sense to use single propert (cert_directory) path in spec? If so an \"external\" flag can be under under \"tls_info\" block and that can be used determine if external cert is required.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 93,
        "name": "Vijay Venkatesh Kumar",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "vijayv81@gmail.com",
        "username": "vv770d"
      },
      "updated": "2020-07-02 14:48:19.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "482726eb_cfaf2a5d",
      "file_path": "mod/component-json-schemas/component-specification/dcae-cli-v2/component-spec-schema.json",
      "patchset_number": 14,
      "line": 818,
      "message": "Finally I got it and instructed team to remove these 3 properties from component specs.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5775,
        "name": "Pawel Baniewski",
        "display_name": "Pawel Baniewski",
        "email": "pawel.baniewski@nokia.com",
        "username": "baniewsk"
      },
      "updated": "2020-07-02 15:15:03.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "03af41d5_fb0b17f4",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "72ae2476_0028b0a2",
      "file_path": "mod/component-json-schemas/component-specification/dcae-cli-v2/component-spec-schema.json",
      "patchset_number": 15,
      "line": 810,
      "message": "Definitely cert_directory!\n\nHmmm, I was thinking about this. Probably I was wrong. We can use the same K8s ephemeral volume between two init containers (DCAE TLS init and CMPv2 init) and application container. Some days ago I have sent to you my idea:\n\n•\tRegarding reusing certdirectory: \no\tWe can use such property, but within provided directory create subdirectory (e.g. external) to avoid name conflicts.\n\n\nSo, property can be one, but K8s plugin in env property for CMPv2 init container will append cert_directory with /external.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5775,
        "name": "Pawel Baniewski",
        "display_name": "Pawel Baniewski",
        "email": "pawel.baniewski@nokia.com",
        "username": "baniewsk"
      },
      "updated": "2020-07-02 15:15:03.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "19a4e838_9a001724",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "cad7af83_37269113",
      "file_path": "mod/component-json-schemas/component-specification/dcae-cli-v2/component-spec-schema.json",
      "patchset_number": 15,
      "line": 810,
      "message": "This will also simplify K8s resources cause we don't have to create new K8s ephemeral volume.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5775,
        "name": "Pawel Baniewski",
        "display_name": "Pawel Baniewski",
        "email": "pawel.baniewski@nokia.com",
        "username": "baniewsk"
      },
      "updated": "2020-07-02 15:20:36.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "72ae2476_0028b0a2",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "a01aaf6f_5fe30744",
      "file_path": "mod/component-json-schemas/component-specification/dcae-cli-v2/component-spec-schema.json",
      "patchset_number": 15,
      "line": 810,
      "message": ">>So, property can be one, but K8s plugin in env property for CMPv2 init container will append cert_directory with /external.        \nYes, I agree. \nWe can reuse \"cert_directory\" - ineffect the external/CMPv2 dependent config can be driven in bp-gen by single flag (use_external_tls) under \"tls_info\" block in spec.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 93,
        "name": "Vijay Venkatesh Kumar",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "vijayv81@gmail.com",
        "username": "vv770d"
      },
      "updated": "2020-07-02 16:57:23.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "cad7af83_37269113",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "03a0c64b_77de390b",
      "file_path": "mod/component-json-schemas/component-specification/dcae-cli-v2/component-spec-schema.json",
      "patchset_number": 15,
      "line": 810,
      "message": "Can be done, but few issues I would like to be addressed, assuming we add use_external_tls to tls_info.\n1. Should the use_external_tls flag be a required field of tls_info?\n1a. If required - schema won't be backward compatibile so we should create dcae-cli-v3 schema? Should we anyhow use dcae-cli-v3-draft, as far is I have seen it has errors and is missing some stuff from dcae-cli-v2.\n1b. If not required - how null value should be handled? Should it default to false or should it skip adding external tls to blueprint?\n2. Is current output of bpgenerator satysfying? Meaning that tls_info and exteral_tls_info should be left as separate objects or put together somehow?",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6044,
        "name": "Remigiusz Janeczek",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "remigiusz.janeczek@nokia.com",
        "username": "rjanecze"
      },
      "updated": "2020-07-03 09:21:43.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "a01aaf6f_5fe30744",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "0bd38491_6d54f0e1",
      "file_path": "mod/component-json-schemas/component-specification/dcae-cli-v2/component-spec-schema.json",
      "patchset_number": 15,
      "line": 810,
      "message": "Hi Remiguiusz, \n1. use_external_tls should be optional\n1.b - If use_external_tls  is not specified,  skip adding external tls to blueprint\n2. I believe separate object for tls_info and external_tls_info on the blueprint is preferred (I dont see the example, is that something you can add part of test resource for each of spec included)? Also you could add a case for both use_tls and use_external_tls as true in test (though current components will not need it, will be good to include it under test)",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 93,
        "name": "Vijay Venkatesh Kumar",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "vijayv81@gmail.com",
        "username": "vv770d"
      },
      "updated": "2020-07-03 15:16:59.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "03a0c64b_77de390b",
      "unresolved": true
    },
